HappyShop project - catalogue category

purpose:
manages product information, inventory, search and browsing functionality

Product:

Purpose:
    represents a product item in the shop with all its details and attribtues

properties:
    -productId: unique identifier for the product
    -prodcutName: name/title of the product
    -description: detailed description of the product
    -price: current selling price
    -quantities: Available stock quantity
    -category: product category (Electronics, clothing, books)
    -imageURL: path to product image
    -manufacturer: brand or manufacturer name
    -dataAdded: when product was added to catalogue

responsibilities:
    -stores all product information
    -provides getter/setters for product properties
    -may include validation for price, quantities, etc.
    -calculates discounted price if applicable

usage:
    created when new product are add to the system. Retrieved when customers browser or search for product.
    updated when inventory changes or prices are modified

order:
    Purpose:
    Represents a customer's order containing products to be purchased.

    Properties:
    - orderId: Unique identifier for the order
    - customerId: ID of the customer who placed the order
    - orderDate: When the order was created
    - orderStatus: Current status (PENDING, PROCESSING, SHIPPED, DELIVERED, CANCELLED)
    - totalAmount: Total cost of all items in the order
    - shippingAddress: Delivery address for the order
    - paymentMethod: How customer will pay (CREDIT_CARD, DEBIT_CARD, PAYPAL)
    - orderItems: List of Product objects and quantities in the order

    Responsibilities:
    - Stores all order information and items
    - Calculates total order amount including taxes and shipping
    - Tracks order status throughout fulfillment process
    - Provides getters/setters for order properties
    - Validates order data before processing

    Key Methods:
    - addProduct(product, quantity): Adds a product to the order
    - removeProduct(productId): Removes a product from the order
    - calculateTotal(): Computes total cost of order
    - updateStatus(newStatus): Changes order status
    - getOrderSummary(): Returns formatted order details

    Usage:
    Created when customer proceeds to checkout from shopping cart. Used by
    OrderProcessing to manage order fulfillment. Retrieved by customers to
    track their order history. Updated by staff when processing and shipping
    orders.

StockLevelIdicator:
    Purpose:
    Provides visual and logical indicators of product availability status based
    on current stock levels.

    Stock Status Levels:
    - IN_STOCK: Product has sufficient quantity available (quantity > 10)
      * Display: Green indicator, "In Stock"
      * Customer can order any quantity up to available stock

    - LOW_STOCK: Product has limited quantity (1-10 items)
      * Display: Yellow/Orange indicator, "Only X left in stock"
      * Warns customer that supply is limited
      * May trigger restock alert for staff

    - OUT_OF_STOCK: Product has zero quantity
      * Display: Red indicator, "Out of Stock"
      * Customer cannot add to cart
      * Shows "Notify me when available" option

    - DISCONTINUED: Product no longer sold
      * Display: Grey indicator, "No longer available"
      * Cannot be ordered
      * May suggest alternative products

    Responsibilities:
    - Determines stock status based on Product quantity
    - Provides appropriate status messages and colors for UI
    - Triggers alerts when stock levels are low
    - Handles threshold calculations for different status levels
    - May implement custom thresholds per product category

    Key Methods:
    - getStatus(product): Returns current stock status
    - getStatusMessage(product): Returns display text (e.g., "3 left in stock")
    - getStatusColor(): Returns color code for UI (GREEN, YELLOW, RED, GREY)
    - isAvailableForPurchase(): Boolean check if can be ordered
    - shouldRestock(product): Checks if restock alert needed
    - setLowStockThreshold(threshold): Customizes low stock level
    - getStockPercentage(product): Returns stock level as percentage

    Usage:
    Used by UI when displaying products to show availability status with
    appropriate colors and messages. Called by Product class to determine
    if item can be added to cart. Used by inventory management system to
    generate restock alerts. Checked by Order processing before confirming
    purchases.